quran[26]{c,v,t}:
  23,93,"SAY: \"My Lord, will you show me what they are threatened with"
  23,94,"My Lord, do not place me among such wrongdoing folk"
  23,95,We are Able indeed to show you whatever We are threatening them with
  23,96,Repay evil with something that is finer; We are quite Aware of anything they describe
  23,97,"SAY: \"My Lord, I seek refuge with You from the devils promptings"
  23,98,"I seek refuge with you, my Lord, lest they accompany me"
  23,99,"since whenever death comes to any one of them, he says: \"My Lord, send me back"
  23,100,"so I may act honorably with anything I may have left behind\"´ Indeed not! It is merely a remark he is making. Beyond them there lies a barrier till the day when they will be raised up again"
  23,101,"Once the Trumpet is blown, no ties of kinship will exist between them on that day, nor may they question one another"
  23,102,Those whose scales are heavy will be prosperous
  23,103,while those whose scales are light will be the ones who have lost their souls; they will remain in Hell
  23,104,The fire will scorch their faces while they will glower away in it
  23,105,Were My signs not recited to you as you (all) were rejecting them
  23,106,"They will say: \"Our Lord, our misery has overwhelmed us and we were errant folk"
  23,107,"Our Lord, get us out of here! If we ever should return [to disobedience], then we would indeed be wrongdoers"
  23,108,"He will say: \"Sink down into it, and never speak to Me"
  23,109,"A group of My servants used to say: ´Our Lord, we believe, so forgive us and have mercy on us; You are the Best One to show mercy!´"
  23,110,You took them for a laughingstock until they made you forget to remember Me since you had been laughing so hard at them
  23,111,I have rewarded them today for how patient they have been; they are triumphant
  23,112,"He will say [further]: \"How many years did you stay on earth"
  23,113,"They will say: \"We stayed a day or part of a day. Ask the timekeepers"
  23,114,"He will say: \"You only lasted a little while, if you only realized it"
  23,115,Did you reckon We have created you just for fun and that you would never be returned to Us
  23,116,"Exalted is God, the true King! There is no deity except Him, Lord of the Noble Throne"
  23,117,"Anyone who appeals to any other deity along with God (Himself), has no proof for it. His reckoning rests only with his Lord. Disbelievers will not succeed"
  23,118,"SAY: \"My Lord, forgive and show mercy! You are the Best One to show mercy"